        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When I use the Db\\NoRecordExists validator with an exclude option as array, I get an PDOException with \"Invalid parameter number: mixed named and positional parameters\". I tracked down the issue to the lines 314 to 317:\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/blob\/master\/library\/Zend\/Validator\/Db\/AbstractDb.php#L314\r\n\r\nWhen I add this line\r\n\r\n  \\Zend\\Debug\\Debug::dump($select->getSqlString());\r\n\r\nbehind the $select->where() call, I get the following output, which shows that the ? is not filled with the value.\r\n\r\n  string(92) \"SELECT \"users\".\"nickname\" AS \"nickname\" FROM \"users\" WHERE `nickname` = :value AND `id` != ?\"\r\n\r\nIf I change the lines 314 to 317 to this single line, it works:\r\n\r\n  $select->where->notEqualTo($this->exclude['field'], $this->exclude['value']);"
        },
